# Greg CRM Walkthrough

Greg CRM is a local-first, agent-native tool. Your data lives inside Markdown files tracking relationships, statuses, and notes while an AI acts synchronously on your behalf through MCP pipelines.

## 1. Local-First Backend Architecture

In this step we replaced synchronous browser `localStorage` and stepped up to a complete Node.js architecture.
All your contact cards are saved directly as [.md](file:///Users/canerden/.gemini/antigravity/brain/bacfe866-205a-4ba5-82e8-fcc3336327de/task.md) files onto your system in the `contacts/` directory. Check them into Git and never get locked out.

![Empty State from the Node Express API](/Users/canerden/.gemini/antigravity/brain/bacfe866-205a-4ba5-82e8-fcc3336327de/main_page_empty_state_1772727425238.png)

## 2. Setting up the Environment
We added a brand new Settings Modal. The UI connects back to Node.js to update the active `.env` file for the app process seamlessly without storing anything dangerous into source code.

This configures the LLM provider mapping out Agent behaviors natively and setting up the Notion Database MCP tokens to pull custom leads directly from Notion.

![Settings UI](/Users/canerden/.gemini/antigravity/brain/bacfe866-205a-4ba5-82e8-fcc3336327de/settings_modal_open_1772727439614.png)

## 3. Beautiful UI & Ergonomics

We built a clean, intuitive, minimalist interface that feels inspired by Folk CRM layout workflows. The app has zero clutter but has highly functional dense cards.

### Dashboard & Sidebar
The Application utilizes a left-hand navigation linking custom filtered groups for "Sales Pipeline", "Investors", or Tags.

![Dashboard Application](/Users/canerden/.gemini/antigravity/brain/bacfe866-205a-4ba5-82e8-fcc3336327de/greg_folk_redesign_1772725322646.webp)

### Pipeline Drag-and-Drop
Moving customers natively across Kanban swim-lanes updates statuses in real time. We built native HTML5 drag logic with visual ghost placements.

![Pipeline State](/Users/canerden/.gemini/antigravity/brain/bacfe866-205a-4ba5-82e8-fcc3336327de/pipeline_view_main_1772725367435.png)

### Detail Panels & Activity Logging
Clicking the user card opens a sleek slide-in drawer. It includes native inline editing for tags, inline select inputs for Status, and automatic visual timeline logs that get saved securely to the [.md](file:///Users/canerden/.gemini/antigravity/brain/bacfe866-205a-4ba5-82e8-fcc3336327de/task.md) format.

![Detail Panel Drawer](/Users/canerden/.gemini/antigravity/brain/bacfe866-205a-4ba5-82e8-fcc3336327de/contact_detail_panel_1772725428090.png)

### High-Density Table Read views
Need to bulk select or scan columns quickly? We implemented an alternating Table layout.

![Table Spreadsheet View](/Users/canerden/.gemini/antigravity/brain/bacfe866-205a-4ba5-82e8-fcc3336327de/table_view_1772725575028.png)
